<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Db_Profiler_Firebug. Query times are passed to firebug as float
without quoting which results as 4 cols table JSON in headers. Eg.:</p>

<p>[0,00011,"SET CHARACTER SET utf8",null]
  ^     ^</p>

<pre><code>result is broken (shifted) table in firebug. eg:
</code></pre>

<p>Time | Event | Parameters             | [null] |
0    | 11    | SET CHARACTER SET utf8 | [null] |</p>

<p>instead of expected:</p>

<p>Time    | Event                  | Parameters |
0,00011 | SET CHARACTER SET utf8 | [null]     |</p>

<p>The problem is only evident when using locales that use commas in float values.</p>

<p>Proposed workaround is to cast query times to string.</p>

